-- Jets’ Tomlinson Tells Radio Station He’s Considering Retirement at Age 32
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-07T14:00:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/jets-tomlinson-tells-radio-station-he-s-considering-retirement.html
New York Jets  running back LaDainian
Tomlinson said in a radio interview he’s considering retirement
from the  National Football League .  Tomlinson, 32, told San Diego radio station XX1090AM
yesterday the main reason he’d return for a 12th season was to
win a championship.  “It’s the first time in my playing career I actually,
honestly thought this may be it for me,” Tomlinson said in the
interview posted on the station’s website  Tomlinson rushed for 280 yards and one touchdown and had 42
catches for 449 yards and two scores in his second season with
the Jets, who missed the playoffs. The fifth-leading rusher in
NFL history with 13,684 yards, he spent his first nine seasons
with the  San Diego Chargers .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  